 "body": "<p>Compensation may arise in a variety of circumstances. This chapter describes the tax treatment of payments and receipts for trading income purposes and covers the following:</p>\n\n<p>For other guidance, see:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/business-income-manual/bim62025\">BIM62025</a> - compensation paid for damages caused by mining operations</li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/business-income-manual/bim40100\">BIM40100</a> onwards and <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/employment-income-manual/eim12852\">EIM12852</a> - treatment of compensation or damages in the hands of the recipient</li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/business-income-manual/bim51425\">BIM51425</a> - compensation payments by brewers to tenants of tied houses</li>\n</ul>\n",
